channel.title: Total
channel.description: Best Drag & Drop Theme for WordPress

item.title: Slider Revolution
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Build beautiful animated sliders with one of the top premium WordPress slider plugins. Use options for ken burns, videos, slider layers, custom fonts and more!

item.title: Templatera
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Templatera makes it easy to create and reuse your page designs. Simply save your Visual Composer layouts after you create them to insert them later.

item.title: Visual Page Builder
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Get the #1 premium WPBakery page builder plugin for FREE with Total. Just point, click, drag & drop to build pixel perfect custom pages the way you want!

item.title: LayerSlider
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Building custom sliders couldnt be easier. Layer Slider includes easy and intuitive layer options so you can build responsive sliders in minutes!

item.title: Uber Menu
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Build a top notch menu with Uber Menu! Total even has a full guide for building out your custom menu with this awesome plugin.

item.title: Post Types Order
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Reorder your blog or custom post type posts the easy way. Simply install the plugin, then drag and drop to reorder your posts.

item.title: Easy Digital Downloads
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Build an e-commerce website with EDD. This powerful and free plugin is fully compatible with Total for easy store building.

item.title: MailChimp
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Total already supports MailChimp, but with the official plugin you can add a subscription widget to grow your newsletter even faster.

item.title: JetPack
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Add Jetpack to Total for added features like site stats, site verification, downtime monitoring, brute force protection, image optimizations and more!

item.title: Akismet
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Protect your website from spam with Akismet the #1 free defense against unwanted attention that could effect your SEO.

item.dc:creator: totalthememain

item.title: Polylang
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Translate your website for FREE with Polylang! Total works seamlessly with this awesome multilingual plugin used by thousands.

item.title: W3 Total Cache
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Total is already one of the fastest themes on the web, but with W3TC theres no way anyone will be able to catchup with your page speeds.

item.title: Contact Form 7
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Create contact forms to stay in touch with your audience. Total supports all Contact Form 7 fields including checkboxes, drop downs, etc.

item.title: Tickera
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Total also works great with the Tickera plugin for WordPress, so you can easily sell events tickets right from your own website.

item.title: Gravity Forms
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Build feature rich contact forms with Gravity Forms plugin, then insert them anywhere with the Visual Composer module.

item.title: Ultimate Addons
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Want even more awesome page building power? Total is fully compatible with the Ultimate Addons plugin for Visual Composer!

item.title: Yoast SEO
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Total supports the popular Yoast SEO plugin, including all of its options for breadcrumbs, SEO titles, page descriptions and more.

item.title: The Event Calendar
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Build a feature rich events page with the Events Calendar or Events Calendar Pro. Total supports both, just pick the one thats right for you!

item.title: WooCommerce
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded: Easily setup your online shop with the very popular WooCommerce plugin for WordPress. Sell your goods and services on your site.

item.title: noriegasaez

item.content:encoded: After some experiences with bloated themes, it was a huge relief working with Total. It's so fast and easy that it actually gets fun (as it always should be). On top of that is a superb customer support, that even gives you snippets to get the work done as your client needs it. Totally recommended. Keep the good work guys!

item.title: bravewhale
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded:
I have consistently come back to Total and use it almost exclusively for all my client's sites and personal sites.
It may not boast the same level of design polish and unique elements as some other top themes, but the benefits of Total are far more valuable. No other theme I've used is as flexible as Total.
Among countless benefits, here are a few of my top reasons for using it:
1. Extensive documentation and snippets for extending the theme. http://wpexplorer-themes.com/total/docs-category/getting-started/ it's truly amazing and so helpful.
2. Edit the name of custom post types. Wanting a post type for "videos" instead of "portfolio" is as easy as renaming and editing it with the built in post type editor.
3. Enable or disabled post types that you aren't using. Other themes force post types to be added to your dashboard.
4. Super clean code, and a lead bloat free core. Easy to edit in a child theme. (though I do wish a child theme came in the download and didn't have to be taken from github).
5. Outstanding support. Fast response time and real solutions to problems.
I think Total really shines in the hands of a designer or developer. If you can use it as a framework to then design and build your own layouts, it will serve you well. Or get a head start with an easy to install demo and build on top of that.
Highly recommended!

The support team is always ready to solve any doubt or issue you could have, and you can count on fast, thoughtful, really helpful answers to your questions, they walk the extra mile to help you make the most of this fantastic, versatile and well designed theme. item.title: onlineministryproject
item.dc:creator: totalthememain
item.content:encoded:
This is the best theme I have ever used.
What I like the most about the theme is how there's a lot of common sense is how it is put together and presented and in how the menus and options are presented.
I think it's very simple to create basically any layout with Total and I like how it's more reactive than responsive, with great little options like showing 2 columns of posts on mobile and 4 on desktop, which makes pages feel like they were truly designed for each device. Visual Composer is implemented really well and it's a great platform with solid extensions and options like saving templates of pages for future use. It's really a killer feature and allows me to put together really content-rich pages quickly.
I recently waited to see how Divi 3.0 would be and I must admit the front-end editor is better than Total, but I still won't switch over, because at the end of the day Total has more options, better white-space out of the box, and a more rich community of extensions and options (Divi has basically none).
Support has always been great for me and the documentation of the theme is second to none, especially with all the snippets allowing you to make cool modifications quickly.
Anyways, just wanted to share some love for the theme. Been a big fan of WPExplorer since the had such a solid list of free themes many years ago and so happy that they continue to grow from strength to strength.
If you're wondering if I'm a paid review, don't worry, this is a real review and you can check out my website at http://bkk.livemusictonight.co to see that I'm totally telling the truth.
Cheers WPExplorer, keep up the good work :)
